TITLE: Confessions of a personal finance reporter (Part Two): 3 more of my worst money mistakes
SUMMARY: Some of you might be simply horrified by my blunders, while others might find them helpful as a way to not manage their personal finances.

TITLE: Should you apply early to college? Here’s what the experts say about this 'strategic game'
SUMMARY: A growing number of high school students are applying early to colleges. "It's turned it into a strategic game," says higher education expert Jeff Selingo.

TITLE: Social Security benefits are set to rise by more than $140 per month in 2023. Here's how to find out how much more money you may receive
SUMMARY: A record high Social Security cost-of-living adjustment will mean bigger monthly benefit checks in 2023. Here's how to gauge the size of your increase.

TITLE: Here's why a new $40,000 electric vehicle tax credit for business owners may be relatively easy to get
SUMMARY: A tax credit for entrepreneurs who buy new electric vehicles or machinery doesn't carry many of the same restrictions that apply to consumers buying clean cars.

TITLE: Investors will be able to contribute up to $22,500 in 401(k) plans and $6,500 in IRAs in 2023
SUMMARY: The IRS has increased the 401(k) contribution limits to $22,500 and individual retirement account limits to $6,500 for 2023. Here's what investors need to know.

TITLE: Biden administration could start forgiving student debt as soon as Sunday
SUMMARY: The Biden administration could start discharging millions of Americans' student debt as soon as Sunday, Oct. 23.

TITLE: Uncertainty clouds holiday shopping for consumers as inflation takes a toll
SUMMARY: To combat higher prices, shoppers plan to make fewer purchases and at a discount this holiday season.

TITLE: Gen Zers are socking away 14% of their income for retirement, a higher share than older adults
SUMMARY: Compared with older generations, young adults also are more confident that their retirement savings is on track.

TITLE: Here's how much you can earn and still pay 0% capital gains taxes in 2023
SUMMARY: The IRS has increased the taxable income thresholds for the 0%, 15% and 20% long-term capital gains brackets for 2023. Here's what investors need to know.

TITLE: Education Department could flag up to 5 million student loan relief applications for review — what to do if yours is among them
SUMMARY: Between 1 million and 5 million student loan borrowers who apply for forgiveness may be asked to provide additional information to verify their eligibility.

TITLE: What a record 8.7% Social Security cost-of-living adjustment could mean for taxes on benefits
SUMMARY: Social Security beneficiaries stand to get the biggest cost-of-living adjustment in 40 years in 2023. Experts say that calls for some strategic tax planning.

TITLE: IRS bumps up estate-tax exclusion to $12.92 million for 2023. Here's what that means for wealthy Americans
SUMMARY: Starting in 2023, individuals can transfer up to $12.92 million to heirs, during life or at death, without triggering a federal estate tax bill.

TITLE: Wisconsin taxpayers' group asks Supreme Court to block Biden student debt relief program
SUMMARY: A taxpayers' group in Wisconsin asked the U.S. Supreme Court to block President Joe Biden's student loan forgiveness plan.

TITLE: The typical U.S. household is spending $445 more a month due to inflation. Here's how to reduce the bite
SUMMARY: Saving money largely comes down to buying cheaper alternatives when possible and finding ways to trim discretionary expenses, according to financial advisors.

TITLE: 66% of American workers are worse off financially than a year ago due to inflation, report finds
SUMMARY: As the cost of living keeps rising, more Americans are struggling financially. Nearly three-quarters have less in savings than last year.

TITLE: IRS: Here are the new income tax brackets for 2023
SUMMARY: The IRS has released higher federal tax brackets and standard deductions for 2023 to adjust for inflation. Here's what filers need to know.

TITLE: Here's what you need to know about 2023 Medicare prescription drug plans during open enrollment
SUMMARY: In addition to checking whether there's a better Medicare coverage option for 2023, you should be aware of some changes to drug coverage.

TITLE: How to get the 'best of both worlds' for Series I bond interest rates before November
SUMMARY: With the interest rate for Series I bonds dropping to roughly 6.48% in November, you can still secure 9.62% for six months before the end of October.

TITLE: Scammers are 'on the move' now that the student loan forgiveness application is live, warns FTC. Watch out for 5 red flags
SUMMARY: Scammers are trying to steal student loan borrowers' money and personal information.

TITLE: 'Know your worth' — 33% of job seekers said they wouldn't even go to a job interview without seeing the salary first
SUMMARY: A strong labor market gives job seekers more leverage when it comes to employee benefits and pay transparency.

TITLE: Your ‘personal inflation rate’ varies by where you live, among other factors
SUMMARY: For the U.S. as a whole, inflation ran at a yearly 8.2% rate in September, but households in some areas of the nation have had it worse.

TITLE: Student loan forgiveness application officially launches, putting relief in sight for 40 million Americans
SUMMARY: Tens of millions of Americans can now apply for student loan cancellation.

TITLE: Here's what to know if you applied for student loan forgiveness during the application beta period
SUMMARY: More than 8 million people applied for student loan forgiveness over the weekend while the application was in a beta test. Here's what they need to know.

TITLE: IRS sends letters to over 9 million who could miss out on valuable 2021 tax credits. Here's how to claim that money
SUMMARY: Individuals and families could be leaving thousands of dollars on the table by not claiming 2021 tax credits. Here's how to get started.

TITLE: Sunflowers, war and drought: Why the price of margarine and butter spiked 32%
SUMMARY: A complex global trade dynamic has fueled tighter supplies of vegetable oils and milk, leading to higher prices for butter and margarine at home.

TITLE: Strategies to navigate the $68 trillion 'great wealth transfer,' according to top-ranked advisors
SUMMARY: Here are four key considerations to help prepare for the biggest wealth transfer ever, according to CNBC's top-ranked financial advisors.

TITLE: In the new thriller 'Emily the Criminal,' director John Patton Ford takes on the student loan crisis
SUMMARY: "Emily the Criminal," a film about a woman who gets involved in credit card fraud, is at heart about the student loan crisis.

TITLE: The 'bummer' of the $7,500 electric vehicle tax credit: Its full value may be hard to get
SUMMARY: The Inflation Reduction Act includes a tax break for consumers who buy electric cars. The tax credit's structure and other requirements create some headwinds.

TITLE: Education Department begins beta testing for student loan forgiveness application
SUMMARY: The Education Department began beta testing the student debt forgiveness application Friday night.

TITLE: Social Security record 8.7% cost-of-living adjustment for 2023 could pressure the program's funds, some experts say
SUMMARY: Social Security beneficiaries are poised to see bigger checks. But it remains to be seen how that will affect the program's long-term funding projections.
